  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_5' aria-label=\" Mahaveer versus State of Maharashtra and Anr pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('5','2025','2025_10_381_394','2025INSC1206'); ><font size='4'> <strong>MAHAVEER<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF MAHARASHTRA AND ANR </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 10 S.C.R. 381</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1206</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004582025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KAROL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASHANT KUMAR MISHRA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the acquittal of the appellant-director of the company was correctly reversed by the High Court and whether his conviction u/ss.39 and 44 of the Electricity Act, 1910 for committing theft of energy and for interference with meters or licensee&rsquo;s use of energy, sustainable. Headnotes&dagger; Electricity Act, 1910 &ndash; ss.39 and 44 &ndash; Theft of energy &ndash; Penalty for interference with meters or licensee&rsquo;s works, and for improper use of energy &ndash; Conviction of the appellant-director of the company for the offence<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 08-10-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2154/2011</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('5','2025','2025_10_381_394','2025INSC1206','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto